$1 $16 c6 (14... bxc4 $143 15. bxc4 dxc4 16. d5 (16. Qe2 Qc6 17. d5 exd5 18.
Nd4 {(Hartston 78)}) 16... exd5 17. e6 $18 {(Geller 76)} fxe6 18. Ne5 {
(Hartston 78)}) 15. c5 Bb4 16. Bc1 $1 a4 $1 17. Nd3 (17. a3 $5 Ba5 18. bxa4
bxa4 19. Qxa4 Qa7 20. Bd2 Bc7 21. Rxb8+ Qxb8 22. Qxc6+ Kf8 23. Ng5 $18 {
(Geller 76)}) 17... Ba5 18. bxa4 bxa4 19. Qxa4 $18 Qa7 20. Bg5 Bc7 {[#]} (20...
Qa6 21. Rb3 Ne7 22. Rfb1 Nd7 23. Ra3 $18 {(Geller 76)}) 21. Rxb8+ $1 Qxb8 (
21... Bxb8 22. Qxc6+ $18) 22. Qxc6+ Kf8 23. Nf4 {"For the exchange White has
two pawns and an enormous attack. The vulner- ability of e6 and g6 to knight
sacrifices makes the black position partic- ularly bad." (Hartston 78)} Ra7 (
23... Rxa2 $2 24. Nh4 Qe8 25. Qxc7 {Pytel}) (23... Ne7 $2 24. Nxe6+ (24. Bxe7+
Kxe7 25. Ng5 $18 {Geller}) 24... fxe6 25. Qxe6 Qe8 26. Nh4 $18 {Hartston}) 24.
Nh4 $1 Qe8 $6 {[#]} (24... Ne7 25. Nxe6+ $1 fxe6 26. Qxe6 Bd8 27. Bxe7+ Bxe7
